											 Rodgers Passes a Winner's Test During American Century Week 
													July 12, 2011 
												 
													By:   Craig Smith   
													 
										 
										 
											 South Shore, Lake Tahoe, Nev. -- Aaron Rodgers figures he is going to be a winner this week, even if he doesn’t take first place at the American Century Championship being played this weekend at Edgewood Tahoe Golf Course in Lake Tahoe, Nev. 
													 
												After a practice round on Tuesday where he interchanged pars and bogeys, Rodgers left for Los Angeles to attend Wednesday’s ESPY Awards, where his Green Bay Packer team is nominated for best team and he is nominated for top male athlete and top NFL player. He will return to Lake Tahoe on Thursday, in plenty of time to get in another practice round before the competition begins on Friday...   full article:  Here   
														 
												 
														 
													  
										 
									 
								 
							 
						 
						 
						 
							 
								 
									 
										 
											  
