											 Golfer Augie Hess Still Beats the Guys and His Age at 96 
													April 24, 2011 
													By:   Craig Smith   
													 
													   Augie Hess Video 1   |      Augie Hess Video 2  
												 
										 
										 
											  
												Bishop, Calif. ? August “Augie” Hess has been playing golf for nearly 50 years. But at age 96, he doesn’t break 90 as often as he used to. 
													 
												Still, he plays well enough to sometimes win his twice-a-week game with his friends at  Bishop Country Club  in Bishop, Calif. He’s already posted an 82 and a couple of 83s this season. He’s never taken a single lesson and never practices his putting, yet he is a solid 18-handicapper on the 6,200-yard, par 71 course that he first joined in 1964. 
												 
													
